article.description: — Max Rice's 28 points helped Boise State defeat Western Oregon 109-70 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Rice puts up 28 in Boise State's 109-70 victory against Western Oregon
article.linkText: Rice puts up 28 in Boise State's 109-70 victory against Western Oregon
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- — Max Rice's 28 points helped Boise State defeat Western Oregon 109-70 on Saturday night. Rice was 7 of 13 shooting, including 6 for 9 from 3-point range, and went 8 for 8 from the line for the Broncos (6-3). Chibuzo Agbo scored 24 points while going 8 of 11 (6 for 8 from 3-point range). Tyson Degenhart was 7 of 9 shooting and 4 of 6 from the free throw line to finish with 18 points. Kris Cook led the way for the Wolves with 17 points. Carson Frincke added 15 points for Western Oregon. Jason Gallant also had 13 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
